description.1: The Man Without Fear and the Black Widow finally tackle the so-called Dark Messiah- while a city quakes beneath their very feet!
description.4: Hulk's wandering in the Canadian wilderness hits a snag when he encounters a legendary creature...with an intense bloodlust. Tremble at the mythic Wendigo!
description.5: Just when things are getting out of hand, the Mandarin strikes where Iron Man least suspects it. Can Tony Stark handle both personas? Or will he have to choose between the two? Its hero vs. businessman in this issue!
description.7: Ulik is trailing Thor once more, but this time...he's not alone. The Thunder God must lunge into action against the mighty Rock Trolls!
description.8: The Thing- vs. the super-powered bombshell named Thundra! Will this issue spell the end for Ben and Alicia?
description.9: Spider-Man butts heads with the Hulk!
description.10: The return of Quicksilver! Thor interrupts an Avengers training session to tell the Avengers he received a galactic transmission from Pietro! Turns out Quicksilver was on Attilan, home planet to the Inhumans, where he was nursed back to health by Inhuman princess Crystal. Now, Quicksilver and Crystal are in love and plan to marry. Following this transmission, the Avengers receive an urgent message from the Xavier Institute where the X-Men are in grave danger!
description.11: Captain America and the Falcon battle Solarr!
description.14: Ka-Zar notices Gemini stealing some Super-Soldier serums!
description.19: Spider-Man and superheroine the CAT take on an all-new man-hating menace: the murderous MAN-KILLER!
description.20: Valkyrie struggles with her aggression towards men, turning to Doctor Strange for advice on finding peace with her teammates. But the Defenders had better learn to get along soon- especially when they must battle mega-robot Omegatron!
description.23: After failing his run at Copperhead Canyon, Johnny Blaze transforms into Ghost Rider to prevent Bart Slade from attempting the stunt. Meanwhile, Roxanne faces the wrath of Snake Dance!
description.24: Adapted from the story by Robert E. Howard.
description.25: Rise of the Dark Messiah! When Daredevil saved a street performer from an attack, he never anticipated that the young man would become his greatest adversary. And with Black Widow out of commission, Daredevil must face Dark Messiah solo!
description.27: When the power of the Witch House falls into the wrong hands, Doctor Strange arrives to halt the threat…only to become into a slave of Dagoth!
description.31: Spider-Man leaves his home turf of New York City - and heads for Asgard! And who else could he be teaming up with there but the MIGHTY THOR, locked in battle with the menace of Kryllk the Cruel!
description.34: Spider-Man vs. the Smasher AND the Disruptor!
description.35: Hawkeye cannot handle the growing romance between the Scarlet Witch and Vision. After blowing off steam in the training room, he decides to leave the team for good. But what has Hawkeye heading out to the West Coast? Wanda grows suspicious of his disappearance and convinces her teammates that the "real" Hawkeye would never leave without a proper farewell.
description.36: Still reeling from the Viper's poison, Steve Rogers has been arrested by the NYPD!
description.37: Captain Marvel is assaulted by his closest allies! What menace could be responsible for this?
description.38: Birth of the Beast. See how Hank McCoy went from man to mutant to...monster?
description.42: Still riled by Betty's marriage, Hulk pays a not-so-friendly visit to Canada. Will Beast of the X-Men be able to talk, (or smack) some sense into Ol' Greenskin? And will Beast be able to keep his true appearance secret from Vera Cantor?
description.43: Iron Man races back to the Avengers mansion to warn everyone about Thanos. Meanwhile, Iron Man learns of Rasputin's plans for doomsday! Can Iron Man all of this on his own? Plus: Beware the fury of Fangor the monster that walks like a man!
description.45: Who is the Demon Druid, and will he prevent Thor from being reunited with Lady Sif? Check out this smack down in London town!
description.47: The Inhumans take center stage, as the ominous behemoth called Omega emerges! Plus, the most shock-laden epilogue you won't want to miss.
description.49: To save a man's life, Night Nurse must thwart a dangerous gunman.
description.51: While Black Widow takes Daredevil to a hospital to treat his gunshot wound, Man-Bull tampers with the water supply of San Francisco! He adds an ingredient- the same serum that’s transformed him into a Man-Bull! Widow tries to save the day, but fails. Is the entire city doomed?
description.54: The Hulk mindlessly trails Betty Ross, in the vain hope that Banner can make amends with his lost love. But when Hulk does reach Niagara Falls, a bigger problem lies in wait- enter Tiger Shark!
description.55: The First Appearance of Thanos, the Mad Titan who would possess the Infinity Gauntlet!  Iron Man confronts the dual threat of the Blood Brothers! Guest-starring Drax the Destroyer!
description.57: The 4-D Man's first appearance! The Asgardians attempt to hold down the fort at Avengers Mansion...but all is not well.
description.58: The Human Torch and Quicksilver battle each other, and a maddening new menace, in the land of the uncanny Inhumans! Will Human Torch be accepted by Crystal's family?
description.61: Ka-Zar battles — in the heart of a hostile city!
description.65: After returning from a Hell dimension where he was forced to duel his ""father"", Johnny Blaze ends up on the wrong side of Sam Silvercloud, an Apache tribesman who wants to prevent Copperhead Canyon from becoming a tourist attraction for stunt riders.
description.66: The Valkyrie is born! Astride her winged horse Aragorn, the warrior goddess vows to protect Asgard. Enchantress may have imbued Barbara Norris with power, but she taketh away from Black Knight. Now, Dane Whitman has turned to stone!
description.67: The man responsible for the creation of the Smasher stands revealed! Enter the Disruptor!
description.68: The Vision makes his final decision about receiving a human body. Will he betray his teammates for a chance of humanity?
description.69: It's Round 2 for the Falcon, and the Viper! This time, the antidote for the Viper's poison is a swift kick to the face!
description.73: Hell-bent on exacting revenge, Man-Bull charges to San Francisco! The Bull and Daredevil paw the ground, lower their horns, and buck heads!
description.74: As one enemy is defeated, another rises…Before freeing Clea and Wong from becoming the next sacrifices to Shuma-Gorath, Doctor Strange must first battle N'Gabthoth, the Shambler of the Sea!
description.75: The Hulk is back on earth at last! But so is...the ever-awesome Abomination! It's a serious slugfest.
description.76: This issue-The Clash of titans! Iron Man versus Namor, the Sub-Mariner!
description.78: Out of the frying pan...into more mystic madness! Thor defeats Absorbing Man only to be confronted by Loki's hounds from Hel. Plus, where are Sif and Karnilla headed?
description.80: Is this the end of the Frightful Four? Plus, the FF trembles at the might of...Thundra! Will this latest recruit hold the key to the Frightful Four's victory?
description.85: A two-on-two showdown! Spider-Man and the ever-lovin', blue-eyed Thing find themselves caught in the center of a contest between the Mad Thinker and the Puppet Master! The object of the game! KILL YOUR HERO FIRST!
description.88: The Juggernaut hurtles back to Earth and drops right in the path of Beast!
description.94: Black Panther, Scarlet Witch, Iron Man, and Hawkeye are still the prisoners of the Space Phantom and Grim Reaper. Captain America uses his past memories of fighting HYDRA to find his missing teammates. Meanwhile, Vision continues to brood over the offer of putting his mind in Wonder Man's body.
description.95: In a harrowing encounter with the Viper both Captain America and the Falcon are poisoned! Will they be able to rid themselves of the Viper's toxin in time?
description.96: Dr. Mynde...man, monster OR BOTH!? The day of the Android Man has come.
description.98: Night Nurse is involved in a dangerous surgery, that if not handled correctly, will prove disastrous for everyone at Metro-General Hospital.
description.99: The Indestructible Man’s tearing through San Francisco and nothing can stop him! It’s up to Daredevil and Black Widow to try, but how do you defeat the Indestructible Man?

1.text: The Man Without Fear and the Black Widow finally tackle the so-called Dark Messiah- while a city quakes beneath their very feet!

12.text: Luke Cage is hired by a mysterious businessman to track a couple of thugs who have stolen technology from the client’s personal cache. Cage accepts the job, but quickly finds out the ‘thugs’ are actually robots! Caught off-guard, Cage struggles put up a fight! Plus, the appearance of a surprise super-villain!

13.text: Jennifer Kale’s grandfather and his cult of sorcerers are in way over their heads! When an occultist text goes missing, (actually burned by Jennifer), all is chaos in the Nether-Spawn’s realm. Man-Thing's restored to Ted Sallis, the scientist who became the muck monster. Will Sallis abandon his role as Man-Thing when tempted by earthly pleasures?

14.text: Ka-Zar notices Gemini stealing some Super-Soldier serums!

16.text: Invaders from the deep! Namor and Lorvex engage in full-scale battle with the surface world to rescue Tamara. Will Namor become Prince of Atlantis once more?

17.text: The Cat’s hyper senses pick up the trail of one Commander Kraken! And a lake house retreat goes to the dogs!

18.text: The Hour of the Bull is near for Shanna, Queen of the Jungle!

19.text: Spider-Man and superheroine the CAT take on an all-new man-hating menace: the murderous MAN-KILLER!

21.text: Reprinting material from Lorna the Jungle Queen #6, Jungle Action Vol. 1 #6, and Jann of the Jungle #9.

25.text: Rise of the Dark Messiah! When Daredevil saved a street performer from an attack, he never anticipated that the young man would become his greatest adversary. And with Black Widow out of commission, Daredevil must face Dark Messiah solo!

27.text: When the power of the Witch House falls into the wrong hands, Doctor Strange arrives to halt the threat…only to become into a slave of Dagoth!

30.text: Namor takes on New York- and Thor, for good measure!

31.text: Spider-Man leaves his home turf of New York City - and heads for Asgard! And who else could he be teaming up with there but the MIGHTY THOR, locked in battle with the menace of Kryllk the Cruel!

32.text: On Christmas Eve, Luke Cage puts the kibosh on criminal activity, all of which has been orchestrated by a mad man named Marley! And this Scrooge plans on detonating a nuclear bomb on Christmas morning! Can Cage prevent this detonation? Or will the blast steal Christmas and millions of lives?

33.text: The origin of Victor Frankenstein! What possessed Europe’s most gifted scholar to create a half-being from the dead? The Monster speaks, and gives his creator a horrifying ultimatum: provide a monster mate…or perish! The Bride of the Monster awakens.

39.text: Janet Pym is transformed into a wasp-humanoid mutate, and Henry desperately tries to escape!

40.text: Hunter Joshua Kane is out for the Werewolf!

46.text: Dracula encounters the granddaughter of one of his oldest foes, Jonathan Harker! Plus, the vampire hunters converge on Dracula's castle. Has the Lord of Vampires finally met his match?

51.text: While Black Widow takes Daredevil to a hospital to treat his gunshot wound, Man-Bull tampers with the water supply of San Francisco! He adds an ingredient- the same serum that’s transformed him into a Man-Bull! Widow tries to save the day, but fails. Is the entire city doomed?

59.text: Luke Cage is hired by Catherine Forsythe, a young woman who believes someone is trying to kill her wealthy grandfather. But when Cage travels to the Forsythe mansion in the country, he runs into deadly robots wearing suits of armor!

60.text: Mark Jackson is a wanted man. One of the few black people in Topequa, Florida, Jackson is now the victim of racial crime, doggedly pursued by corrupt sheriff Wallace Corlee. But the Man-Thing has heard Mark’s plight and understands. Will justice be served in the heart of the swamps?

61.text: Ka-Zar battles — in the heart of a hostile city!

63.text: Lord Vashti introduces Namor to Tamara, a keen and lovely alien from the planet Laab. She may have earned Vashti's trust, what will Tamara win over the scourge of the seas? And is she truly a friend, or foe, to Atlantis?

64.text: Shanna takes on El Montano, a cold-hearted human trafficker and narcotics dealer!

70.text: Reprinting material from Lorna the Jungle Queen #4, Jungle Action Vol. 1 #4, and Jungle Tales #1.

73.text: Hell-bent on exacting revenge, Man-Bull charges to San Francisco! The Bull and Daredevil paw the ground, lower their horns, and buck heads!

74.text: As one enemy is defeated, another rises…Before freeing Clea and Wong from becoming the next sacrifices to Shuma-Gorath, Doctor Strange must first battle N'Gabthoth, the Shambler of the Sea!

79.text: Dracula, now in the past, begins to wreak havoc on the citizens of Transylvania!

83.text: Caught in the crosshairs of the gods! Namor discovers that a beautiful woman he rescued is none other than Venus, Goddess of Love! What will Ares, God of War have to say about Venus' departure to Earth? Namor takes on the God of War in mighty combat!

84.text: Greer Grant stars as The Cat! It’s a Chicago skyline battle as the Cat goes claw-to-talon with The Owl, Daredevil’s enemy!

85.text: A two-on-two showdown! Spider-Man and the ever-lovin', blue-eyed Thing find themselves caught in the center of a contest between the Mad Thinker and the Puppet Master! The object of the game! KILL YOUR HERO FIRST!

89.text: Ant-Man and the Wasp, both still stuck at actual (insect) size, are captured by Para-Man!

90.text: Father Ramon Joquez has been possessed by a 12th century monk with demonic intentions for Jack and the world!

91.text: Luke Cage learns about a band of criminals led by a woman named Black Mariah. Mariah’s thieves pose as ambulance drivers and steal corpses to loot them of possessions! Disgusted by these acts, the Hero for Hire decides to give the city a criminal shakedown on the house.

92.text: Mary Shelley’s classic, resurrected in the mighty Marvel manner! The most spine-tingling read in English literature, Frankenstein tells the tale of the monstrosity in man and man's creation. In the Arctic wild, explorer Robert Walton IV uncovers the body of a creature too nightmarish for words. Behold, the monster of Victor Frankenstein!

99.text: The Indestructible Man’s tearing through San Francisco and nothing can stop him! It’s up to Daredevil and Black Widow to try, but how do you defeat the Indestructible Man?
